🔗 TrustChain
An Autonomous Agent for Ethical Supply Chain Verification

Built with IBM Granite 3.0, IBM Docling, and ALTK

🌍 The Challenge

Global enterprises spend over $50B annually verifying supplier sustainability and compliance claims.

Current approaches struggle because:

Critical data is buried in unstructured documents (PDFs, invoices, reports)

Greenwashing and unverifiable claims are widespread

Manual audits are slow, costly, and prone to human error

💡 The TrustChain Solution

TrustChain is an autonomous, agentic system that continuously validates supplier integrity and ESG claims—at scale.

The agent:

Ingests unstructured supplier documents using IBM Docling

Extracts fine-grained ESG and compliance signals with IBM Granite 3.0

Verifies factual consistency using ALTK self-healing validation loops

Generates a real-time, explainable Trust Score for procurement and compliance teams

This enables faster decisions, reduced risk, and defensible supplier evaluations.

🧠 System Architecture & Tech Stack

LLM Core: IBM Granite 3.0 Instruct (via watsonx.ai)

Document Processing: IBM Docling

Verification Layer: ALTK (Agent Lifecycle Toolkit) for silent review and hallucination mitigation

Agent Orchestration: Custom Python agent using LangChain & Pydantic

🚀 Getting Started
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py sample_invoice.md


Observe the agent as it ingests documents, reasons over extracted data, performs self-correction, and produces a validated trust assessment.